Stock Portfolio Tracker
Overview

The Stock Portfolio Tracker is a Python-based application that allows users to track their stock investments. It enables users to add stocks to their portfolio, remove them, and view real-time stock prices along with portfolio performance.

The tracker fetches current stock prices using the Alpha Vantage API and calculates portfolio value, gains/losses, and performance.
Features

    Add Stock: Add stocks to your portfolio with the option to input purchase price or use the current market price.

    Remove Stock: Remove stocks from your portfolio.

    Update Stock Prices: Update the current price of all stocks in your portfolio.

    View Portfolio: Display a summary of the portfolio including stock values, gains/losses, and overall portfolio performance.

    Persistent Data: The portfolio data is saved in a portfolio.json file, allowing data to persist between program runs.

Requirements

    Python 3.x

    Requests library (Install with pip install requests)

    Alpha Vantage API Key (free account available at Alpha Vantage)

Setup

    Clone this repository to your local machine:

git clone https://github.com/yourusername/stock-portfolio-tracker.git
cd stock-portfolio-tracker

Install required dependencies:

    pip install requests

    Get your Alpha Vantage API Key by signing up for a free account at Alpha Vantage.

    Open the Stock Portfolio Tracker.py file and replace the placeholder API_KEY = 'YOUR_ALPHA_VANTAGE_API_KEY' with your actual API key.

Usage

To start the Stock Portfolio Tracker, run the following command:

python Stock Portfolio Tracker.py

Menu Options

    Add Stock: Add a stock to your portfolio by entering the stock symbol, number of shares, and purchase price (optional).

    Remove Stock: Remove a stock from your portfolio by entering the stock symbol.

    Update Prices: Update the current prices of all stocks in your portfolio.

    View Portfolio: Display a summary of your portfolioâ€™s value, individual stock performance, and overall gains/losses.

    Exit: Exit the application.

Example

Stock Portfolio Tracker
1. Add Stock
2. Remove Stock
3. Update Prices
4. View Portfolio
5. Exit
Enter your choice (1-5): 1
Enter stock symbol: AAPL
Enter number of shares: 10
Enter purchase price (leave blank for current price): 
Added 10 shares of AAPL to your portfolio.

Stock Portfolio Tracker
1. Add Stock
2. Remove Stock
3. Update Prices
4. View Portfolio
